d in writing and are subject to the approval of NSF, who will ensure compliance with all federal, university, and Institutional Review Board policies on the use of restricted data.</span></p>', '<span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;All data will be accessible to the public and subject to usage and dissemination restrictions under the following publication licenses:  __________. (Examples are the CC-0 Public Domain Dedication License, the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY), etc.)&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:4482,&quot;4&quot;:[null,2,15724527],&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;15&quot;:&quot;arial,sans,sans-serif&quot;}">All data will be accessible to the public and subject to usage and dissemination restrictions under the following publication licenses: __________. (Examples are the CC-0 Public Domain Dedication License, the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY), etc.)</span>', '{"meta": {"schemaVersion": "1.0"}, "type": "textArea", "attributes": {"cols": 20, "rows": 2, "asRichText": true}}', 0, 2, @default_funder2_id, CURDATE(), @default_funder2_id, CURDATE());
INSERT INTO versionedQuestions (id, versionedTemplateId, versionedSectionId, questionId, questionText, requirementText, guidanceText, sampleText, json, useSampleTextAsDefault, displayOrder, createdById, created, modifiedById, modified) VALUES (3323, 316, 2007, 968, '<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;What is the long-term strategy for maintaining, curating, and archiving the data?\nNote: The Office of Polar Programs policy requires that metadata files, full data sets, and derived data products be deposited in a long-lived and publicly accessible archive. \nNote: if you plan to submit data to the Arctic Data Center (ADC) please refer to the guidance in the panel on the right.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:963,&quot;3&quot;:[null,0],&quot;4&quot;:[null,2,15987699],&quot;9&quot;:0,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0}"><br />What is the long-term strategy for maintaining, curating, and archiving the data?<br /></span></pNSFsp><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;What is the long-term strategy for maintaining, curating, and archiving the data?\nNote: The Office of Polar Programs policy requires that metadata files, full data sets, and derived data products be deposited in a long-lived and publicly accessible archive. \nNote: if you plan to submit data to the Arctic Data Center (ADC) please refer to the guidance in the panel on the right.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:963,&quot;3&quot;:[null,0],&quot;4&quot;:[null,2,15987699],&quot;9&quot;:0,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:4,&quot;12&quot;:0}"><strong>Note:</strong> The Office of Polar Programs policy requires that metadata files, full data sets, and derived data products be deposited in a long-lived and publicly accessible archive. <br /><strong>Note:</strong> if you plan to submit data to the Arctic Data Center please refer to the guidance in the panel on the right.</span></p>', '', '<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot